//Posterior cruciate ligament (PCL)


Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 05 - Ligaments, joint capsule & menisci of Knee MRI
When I select the radio button 'Finding'
Then 'Finding' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Posterior cruciate ligament (PCL)' from the Finding dropdown menu
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Injury, acute' radio button is enabled
And 'Injury, chronic' radio button is enabled


When I select 'Injury, acute' radio button
Then 'Total rupture' radio button is enabled
And 'Partial rupture' radio button is enabled
And 'Popliteus tendon rupture' checkbox is enabled
And 'Middle third' checkbox is enabled
And 'Proximal third' checkbox is enabled
And 'Distal third' checkbox is enabled


When I select 'Total rupture' radio button
Then 'Signal increase T2w' checkbox is enabled
And 'Thickening' checkbox is enabled
And 'Contusion/BME' checkbox is enabled
And 'Proximal fibula (AO 4F1A1-1)' checkbox is enabled
And 'Lat. tibial plateau (AO 41A1-1)' checkbox is enabled
And 'Med. tibial plateau (AO 41A1-1)' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Contusion/BME' checkbox
Then 'Lateral femur condyle' checkbox is enabled
And 'Anterolateral tibial plateau' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Proximal Fibula (AO 4F1A1-1)' checkbox
Then 'Arcuate sign' checkbox is enabled
When I select 'Arcuate sign' checkbox
Then 'Avulsion fibula' checkbox is enabled
And 'Avulsion of the posterolateral capsule' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Partial rupture' radio button
Then 'Thickening' checkbox is enabled
And 'Signal increase T2w' checkbox is enabled



When I select 'Injury, chronic' radio button
Then 'PCL, without surgery' radio button is enabled
And 'PCL transplant' radio button is enabled

When I select 'PCL, without surgery' radio button
Then 'Signal increase in T2w' checkbox is enabled
And 'Thickening' checkbox is enabled
And 'Synovialization' checkbox is enabled
And 'Ganglion cyst' checkbox is enabled
When I select 'Ganglion cyst' checkbox
Then 'Max. dimension in mm' input field is enabled

When I select 'PCL transplant' radio button
Then 'Graft failure' radio button is enabled
And 'Graft re-rupture' radio button is enabled
And '"Tunnel" cyst' checkbox is enabled
When I select '"Tunnel" cyst' checkbox
Then 'Tibial' checkbox is enabled
And '"Femoral' checkbox is enabled
